CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 14, 1967, pg. 3B reads: "Open House - Dr. and Mrs. Woodford Alvin Harris of Ambridge, Pa., held an open house at the rim of the festive season, honoring daughter Mary Sylvia and Dr. Willis Sanderlin of Washington, D.C. Sharing the delightful and colorful evening were daughter Connie and her husband Hampton Gee also of Washington, and son "Mike" who attends Howard.  Pictured seated are Dr. and Mrs. "Woody" Harris; Standing, Hampton and Connie Gee, Mike Harris, and the newlyweds Dr. and Mrs. Willis Sanderlin. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of five women, one wearing circle patterned dress, and two men wearing dark suits, standing near bar in home of Dr. and Mrs. Woodford "Woody" Alvin Harris during open house party, Ambridge
